function getGrade6Extra() {
  return [
    { title: 'Planning for Middle School', content: 'Next year, I will start middle school. I feel both excited and nervous about this big change. The middle school campus is much larger than my primary school, and I will have different teachers for each subject. I have heard that the homework will be more challenging too. To prepare myself, I am working on improving my study habits this year. I am learning to take notes, manage my time better, and ask questions when I do not understand something. My older cousin told me that making friends is the most important thing in middle school. I hope I will adapt quickly and enjoy this new chapter of my life.' },
    { title: 'The Internet and Learning', content: 'The internet has become an important tool for learning. We can find information about almost any topic within seconds. Educational videos help us understand difficult concepts through visual explanations. Online dictionaries make it easy to look up new English words. However, we must be careful when using the internet. Not all information online is correct or reliable. Our teacher taught us to check multiple sources before believing something we read online. We should also limit our screen time and balance internet use with reading physical books. When used wisely, the internet is a powerful learning tool.' },
    { title: 'A School Performance', content: 'Our class performed a play for the school last month. We chose the story of The Tortoise and the Hare. I played the role of the tortoise. We practiced every afternoon for two weeks. Remembering all my lines in English was challenging, but my classmates helped me practice. On the day of the performance, I was very nervous. When I stepped on stage, I saw hundreds of students watching. But once I started speaking, I forgot my nervousness. The audience laughed and clapped. After the show, our teacher said she was proud of us. The experience taught me that preparation and teamwork lead to success.' },
    { title: 'Saving Pocket Money', content: 'I receive pocket money from my parents every week. Before, I used to spend it all on snacks and toys. But this year, I decided to start saving. I bought a piggy bank and put at least half of my pocket money into it every week. After three months, I had saved enough to buy a book I really wanted. Saving money taught me an important lesson about patience and planning. Now I think carefully before buying anything. I ask myself whether I really need it or just want it for a moment. Learning to manage money is a skill that will be useful for my whole life.' },
    { title: 'Volunteering at the Animal Shelter', content: 'During the winter holiday, my family and I volunteered at a local animal shelter. The shelter takes care of dogs and cats that have no homes. We helped clean the animals cages, prepare food, and walk the dogs. Some animals were shy at first, but they became friendly after we spent time with them. I learned that abandoned animals need love and attention just like pets at home. The experience made me more compassionate towards animals. I plan to volunteer there regularly and encourage my friends to join me. Everyone can make a difference by giving their time and care.' },
    { title: 'The Science Behind Rainbows', content: 'Have you ever wondered how rainbows form? A rainbow appears when sunlight passes through water droplets in the air. White sunlight is actually made up of seven colours: red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, and violet. When light enters a water droplet, it slows down and bends. This is called refraction. The light then reflects off the back of the droplet and bends again as it exits. Different colours bend at slightly different angles, which separates them into the spectrum we see as a rainbow. You can create your own rainbow at home using a garden hose on a sunny day. Science explains many beautiful natural phenomena.' },
    { title: 'Team Sports vs Individual Sports', content: 'Some students prefer team sports like basketball and football, while others enjoy individual sports like swimming or running. Both types have their advantages. Team sports teach cooperation, communication, and how to work towards a common goal. Players learn to trust their teammates and handle both winning and losing together. Individual sports develop self-discipline, personal responsibility, and mental toughness. Athletes compete against themselves to improve their own records. I play badminton individually but also enjoy playing basketball with my classmates. I think trying both types helps develop a well-rounded personality. The most important thing is to find a sport you enjoy and stay active.' },
    { title: 'Writing a Diary in English', content: 'My English teacher suggested that we keep a diary in English. At first, I found it very difficult because I did not know enough words to express my thoughts. I could only write two or three simple sentences. But I kept trying every day. When I did not know a word, I looked it up in the dictionary. After two months of practice, I can now write a full paragraph about my day. Writing a diary has helped me improve my vocabulary and grammar naturally. It also helps me remember happy moments. I suggest all English learners try this method because writing regularly is one of the best ways to improve.' },
    { title: 'Celebrating the Mid-Autumn Festival', content: 'The Mid-Autumn Festival falls on the fifteenth day of the eighth lunar month, when the moon is at its fullest and brightest. This festival is about family reunion and togetherness. On this day, my whole family gathers at my grandparents house. We eat a big dinner together and share mooncakes of different flavours. After dinner, we sit in the garden and admire the bright round moon. My grandmother tells us the legend of Change flying to the moon. I love this festival because it reminds us to appreciate family bonds and the beauty of nature.' },
    { title: 'How to Give a Good Presentation', content: 'Giving presentations is a skill that becomes more important as we grow older. I used to be terrified of speaking in front of my classmates. Then my teacher gave us some useful tips. First, prepare your content well and practice several times at home. Second, make eye contact with your audience instead of just reading from notes. Third, speak clearly and at a moderate pace. Fourth, use simple visual aids like pictures or short bullet points. Fifth, end with a strong conclusion that summarises your main idea. Following these tips has helped me become more confident. I still feel nervous before presentations, but the anxiety decreases with practice.' },
  ];
}

